Okay. And also our data frames and statistical tools, they're deeply embedded into the language.

00:16:12.799 --> 00:16:16.880
And with Python, those, all that stuff, that's all, you know, that all comes from third party

00:16:16.880 --> 00:16:21.919
modules. Now, I think if you're an R user, you know, some of these things are actually not that

00:16:21.919 --> 00:16:27.039
hard to deal with, like one based indexing versus zero based indexing. You know, you can do it.

00:16:27.039 --> 00:16:31.039
It's not that hard. You can do it. It's, it's, it's, it's, it's, it's, it's, it's, it's, it's, it's,

00:16:31.440 --> 00:16:35.840
you can do it. It's not that hard to, to, to switch from, from one to the other.

